Project Summary
  • Brainstormed solutions to solve low user retention by adding a feature that prompts to user to post content about
  • Conducted user surveys to identify that the issue stemmed from a lack of inspiration
  • Designed and prototyped the feature on Figma by meeting the client and gaining valuable feedback about the product
Eunoia UX Design Jam
Participated in my 1st UX Design Jam (Design Hackathon) where my group was tasked with finding a design solution for our client: UX Was Here to tackle various challenges in a week duration. UX was Here (UwH) is a collaborative platform where UX enthusiasts.
Our group of 4 consisted of 3 technically skilled students and 1 design student (that is I) where I took the Creative Lead and overlooked prototyping of the proposed solution on Figma.
Design Framing
UX Was Here was struggling with getting people to post compelling content and promote app usage. Through our research, we framed our problem statement as:

How might we help assist UX professionals find value, in giving back to the community by providing insights, sharing resources and engaging in activities to foster learning?
Design Process:
  • Searched for values and pillars of client:
    Value collaboration & inclusivity towards new comers seeking to explore the field of UX.
  • Narrowed it down to a target audience:
    Users who are professional designers, specifically those who do not directly contribute to content creation
  • Conducted user research:
    Concluded with many professionals wanting to give back to community & mentor newer designers as a learning opportunity for themselves learning
  • Created a solution with insights:
    Our solution is to allow UX was Here to provide community with prompts as a way of community engagment
Challenges and design solutions:
  1. Main Problem: High user turn rate and Low user retention.
    Solution: Created a promt topic feature to write and post content and solving low user engagement.

  2. Understanding the needs and motivation of its users. Solution: Conducted surveys among UX Professionals to gain feedback about their engagemnet with the platform.

  3. Effective onboarding of new users. Solutions: Suggested a walkthrough of the platform as user starts engaging with it.
Learning Outcomes
  1. Understanding a real life client needs and goals to effectively conduct user research.
  2. Learning how to effectively conduct primary and secondary research to frame a problem.
  3. Work in an collaborative environment as the creative lead and undertaking assignments to carry project to completion.
More About the Solution:
UX professionals who find value in giving back to the community can benefit from narrowed topic suggestions. This eliminates the tedious process of coming up with a post idea. Providing designers with the opportunity to pick between prompted discussion topics would serve as an incentive to contribute to a learning community where they might gain the satisfaction of contributing to the learning development of newer designers.
